body:
1 more week

1 more week until i get off early per my request because of a “prior engagement”.

1 more week until I see my best friend again since she’ll be back from her trip.

1 more week until i’m packing sandwiches to eat for dinner in line since there is very little to eat at the stadium.

1 more blessed week until i put on my pom pom head band, glittery fanny pack and of course my reputation t-shirt.

1 more week.

1 more week until i get to experience the show of a lifetime at FedEx field,

1 more week until i sing back to Taylor Every. Single. Song.

1. more. week.

I don’t think i have ever been so excited.

summary: by Brian Cantor - 2 July 2018 Thanks to another week of solid sales and big gains on the radio front, Taylor Swift’s “Delicate”...
caption:
by Brian Cantor - 2 July 2018

Thanks to another week of solid sales and big gains on the radio front, Taylor Swift’s “Delicate” reaches a new peak on the Billboard Hot 100.

The song, which was #27 last week, soars to #20 this week. It had never previously gone higher than #25.

As noted, “Delicate” enjoyed a particularly strong week at radio. It reached #1 on the hot adult contemporary format and moved closer to the Top 5 at pop. It also posted gains at adult contemporary and rhythmic.

A true radio hit, “Delicate” takes #4 on this week’s edition of the all-format Billboard Radio Songs chart.

“Delicate” follows official singles “Look What You Made Me Do,” “Ready For It” and “End Game” and promotional single “Gorgeous” in becoming the fifth Top 20 hit from Swift’s “reputation” album.
